## 8. Purchase History & Reporting Fields

Every sale a customer makes links back to their record (per Sales Management), which is what populates:

- **Purchase History** — a running list of past invoices, viewable from Customer Detail.
- **Purchase Frequency** and **Lifetime Spend** — both explicitly noted in the client's sheet as feeding the Customer Report (see the future Reports module document).

**Drill-down behavior:** Purchase History isn't just a static summary — each row is clickable and opens that transaction's own full detail screen:

|From Customer Detail|Opens|
|---|---|
|Click a Purchase History row|The full **Sales/Invoice Detail** screen for that sale (line items, composition breakdown, batch sold from, discount/tax math, advance payment, delivery status) — as described in the Sales Management document|
|Click a Return/Exchange row|The full **Sales Return Detail** screen for that transaction (return or exchange fee, item condition, linked original invoice) — as described in the Sales Return document|

This keeps Customer Detail as a clean index of everything tied to that customer, while each transaction's full detail — including anything that shouldn't be visible to every role — lives on its own screen, governed by that screen's own role visibility rules. (Note: unlike Supplier, Sales/Invoice Detail is already visible to Sales Team per the Sales Management role table, so there's no extra restriction introduced by drilling in from Customer Detail.)

